MapsSuggestions Network Defaults

[ Last update on 2018-07-27 at 12:01:21, by Ruchi Khandelwal ]

This is a list of all the 330 constants that are defined using the MapsSuggestions built-in network-defaults system, a convenience and type-safe layer built on top of GEODefaults. They can easily be set at run-time using the command line, which may facilitate testing. They can also be set over the network to alter software that has already shipped, running on customer devices.

The system is used in MapsSuggestions.framework, destinationd, NavdDoom, Maps Supergreen, as well as in some code that has a close relation to MapsSuggestions.

To set a value, simply run the following as mobile on the device where you want them. That device is probably the phone, but it may be a watch as well.

An example:

defaults write com.apple.GEO MapsSuggestionsRoutineSourceEnabledKey -bool NO

... or ...

defaults write com.apple.GEO MapsSuggestionsTrackerETAFreshTimeKey -float 120.0

... depending on the type. Check the list below to see what override type belongs to what ObjC type. Using the wrong one will likely result in crashes.

To update this document, cd into your source directory (the one that contains Maps, GeoServices, etc.) and run:

MapsTools/Scripts/extractMapsSuggestionsDefaults.py > Maps/iOS/Suggestions/MapsSuggestionsDefaults.html

Try to do this within every commit that changes or adds any of these. Please, do not modify this document by hand!.
For all questions, see Tim Aerts or anyone close to MapsSuggestions.

MSPUpNextMaximumAllowableHorizontalAccuracyInMetersKey
We don't allow locations any less accurate than this to be used to filter out whether a Supergreen suggestion is nearby.

MapsSuggestions Network Defaults

[ Last update on 2018-07-27 at 12:01:21, by Ruchi Khandelwal ]

This is a list of all the 330 constants that are defined using the MapsSuggestions built-in network-defaults system, a convenience and type-safe layer built on top of GEODefaults. They can easily be set at run-time using the command line, which may facilitate testing. They can also be set over the network to alter software that has already shipped, running on customer devices.

The system is used in MapsSuggestions.framework, destinationd, NavdDoom, Maps Supergreen, as well as in some code that has a close relation to MapsSuggestions.

To set a value, simply run the following as mobile on the device where you want them. That device is probably the phone, but it may be a watch as well.

An example:

defaults write com.apple.GEO MapsSuggestionsRoutineSourceEnabledKey -bool NO

... or ...

defaults write com.apple.GEO MapsSuggestionsTrackerETAFreshTimeKey -float 120.0

... depending on the type. Check the list below to see what override type belongs to what ObjC type. Using the wrong one will likely result in crashes.

To update this document, cd into your source directory (the one that contains Maps, GeoServices, etc.) and run:

MapsTools/Scripts/extractMapsSuggestionsDefaults.py > Maps/iOS/Suggestions/MapsSuggestionsDefaults.html

Try to do this within every commit that changes or adds any of these. Please, do not modify this document by hand!.
For all questions, see Tim Aerts or anyone close to MapsSuggestions.
